name: Hayden Library 3rd and 4th floor
directions: Directions are the same for 3rd and 4th floors. Go to Hayden Library's entrance by going down the outside stairs or taking the elevator the left of the stairs. Enter the front doors and go right. Go up the stairs to the left of the computers. At the top of the stairs, go to the elevators straight ahead. Go to the 3rd or 4th floor. On either floor, exit the elevator and go right. The single-use restroom is the last door on the right before the book shelves.
comment: 4th floor has a special high-seat toilet for wheelchair users. 4th floor bathroom is smaller but less frequently used.

name: College Avenue Commons Arizona State University - 3rd floor
directions:
STAIRS ROUTE: Go up the outside stairs on the east side of the building to the third floor. Enter the door on your left to enter the building. (If it's locked, turn to your left and try the door on the other side of the stairwell.) Go down the hallway to the right and take the first right after that. There are 2 single-use bathrooms on the right. (If you took the alternate door, go inside, take your first right, go down the hallway past the wide staircase, take the first right after that, and there are 2 single-use bathrooms on the right.)

ELEVATOR ROUTE: From outside on the east side of the building, go inside the glass doors to the left of the stairs. Go up the elevator to the third floor. Exit the elevator and go down the main hallway. Continue down the hallway past the wide indoor staircase. Take the first right after the staircase. There are 2 single-use bathrooms on the right.
comment: Building hours are 7am-7pm. Students and janitors occasionally exit after 7pm and you may be able to catch the door. The left bathroom has a shower.

name: College Avenue Commons Arizona State University - 2nd floor
directions:
Stairs route: Go up the outside stairs on the east side of the building to the second floor. Go to the short hallway to the left of and slightly hidden by the second flight of stairs. The door on the left requires ASU Sun Card access and has two gender neutral bathrooms inside.

Elevator route: From outside on the east side of the building, go inside the glass doors to the left of the stairs. Go up the elevator to the second floor. Exit the elevator and take a left out the doors to the outside. Take a sharp left and head toward the glass doors. The door on the left requires ASU Sun Card access and has two gender neutral bathrooms inside.
comment: ASU Sun Card required. For elevator use, building hours are 7am-7pm. Students and janitors frequently exit during the middle of the day on weekdays. Non-ASU Sun Card bathrooms available on 3rd floor.

name: Boom Burger

comment: Building hours for public washrooms are: Mon-Sat: 11am-10pm, Sun: 11am-4pm.

There is a second single-occupancy gender neutral restroom in the conference room on the first floor but that part of the building is behind the reception desk and not accessible to the public unless you have business in the back part of the building, also the conference room is sometimes in use.
comment: This building has a prominent sign on the door advertising it is a safe space for LGBTQ people.

name: Colorful Yun Nan (C.Y.N.)
directions: Two single-occupancy restrooms in rear. Restrooms are ambiguously marked, both have one sign saying "men" and "women" but also have a second sign designating both as unisex. I've seen people of various genders using both restrooms.
comment: This is a Chinese restaurant and it's not super high traffic, people might notice if you just came in to use the restroom, especially if it was not a crowded time. Good authentic Yunnan Chinese food too.

name: Ali Baba Middle Eastern Restaurant & Hookah Bar
directions: Three single-occupancy restrooms. One is specifically marked as unisex/gender neutral. Restrooms are in the hallway in the back of the restaurant, to the side of the dining area.
comment: This is a restaurant and hookah bar. Especially at night when the hookah bar is busy, it would be easy to duck in here without anyone noticing.

name: Teviot Row House, Edinburgh, Edinburgh EH8 9AJ, UK

name: The Music Store, Inc.
directions: On the back of the store, toward the very left corner.
comment: I discovered it once on one of their event days when they were really busy. The salespeople will want to help you, and I'm not sure what they'd say if you went in just to use the bathroom. You could at least pretend to be amused by all of the shiny instruments!

name: Oklahoma Jazz Hall of Fame
directions: Not immediately visible. After going through the entrance, you'll have to take quite a walk back to a hallway that looks like where the offices might be. At the end of the hallway there are a number of bathrooms - two women's, one men's, and one single-use unisex/family restroom.
comment: I have been here for numerous musical events and rehearsals over the last few years. A couple of those times the unisex/family restroom has been locked. One of those times I was to be there all day, and I went and found one of the staff members and told her I was uncomfortable with using the other restrooms - she unlocked it for me without any trouble.

Open only in the mornings, as is standard for many donut shops!
